- Implemented a right-side Desktop Widgets sidebar featuring 6 modular cards: Calendar/Cron, Hardware Monitor, Network Speed, Download Queue, Quick Note, and Now Playing. Added global music event dispatching (`clawos-music-state` and `clawos-music-toggle`) into `LocalMusicApp` and `MusicApp` to synchronize playback state with the desktop widget. Added a toggle to enable/disable widgets in the OS Personalization settings. Bumped version to v1.2.0.
- Re-architected Desktop Widgets to use a fixed width (`600px`), strict `grid-cols-2 grid-rows-3` layout with a unified `h-[160px]` height for each card to fix layout-breakage on 125% browser zoom. Fixed network speed text overflowing the card by applying `truncate` and reducing font size. Fixed music state bug by adding a `clawos-music-request` event so the widget can actively poll current playback state upon mount. Bumped version to v1.2.1.
- Massively upgraded the Now Playing widget. Replaced the simplistic `clawos-music-state` system with a robust `clawos-music-sync` bridge. The widget now actively displays the app source (Local vs Netease), the cover art, title, artist, and **real-time synced lyric line**. Implemented bidirectional controls (Prev, Play/Pause, Next) via a new `clawos-music-cmd` event that dispatches exact commands to the currently active audio provider. Bumped version to v1.2.2.
- Debugged and fixed the "Now Playing" desktop widget data synchronization issues: `MusicApp.tsx` and `LocalMusicApp.tsx` were incorrectly passing data mappings (e.g. mapping `title` to `currentSong.name` which was undefined in MusicApp), leading to the widget displaying "未知歌手" in place of the song name. Fixed the property mapping to `currentSong.title`.
- Adjusted widget typography based on user feedback to emphasize the Song Name (`text-base font-black`) and correct the layout hierarchy over the Artist label. Removed stale `clawos-music-state` listeners to prevent state pollution. Bumped version to v1.2.3.
- Replaced the brittle desktop music event chain with a persistent in-memory bridge at `frontend/src/lib/musicBridge.ts`. The widget now subscribes to a unified state store instead of relying on one-shot `clawos-music-request` timing, so returning to the desktop immediately restores the latest known playback state.
- Added explicit playback ownership arbitration between Netease and Local Music. When one source enters `preparing` or `playing`, it becomes the active owner and the bridge automatically sends `pause` to the previous owner, preventing dual playback and card flicker.
- Updated both `MusicApp.tsx` and `LocalMusicApp.tsx` to report `preparing/playing/paused` states and push metadata before actual audio playback starts, improving perceived responsiveness of the desktop "Now Playing" card.
- Added frontend regression tests for late state restoration, listener notification, active-owner command routing, and dual-source conflict handling. Bumped version to v1.2.4.
- Simplified the Baidu/Quark netdisk onboarding flow. Added `GET /api/system/netdisk/status` to distinguish mounted, not-mounted, expired-auth, and backend-unreachable states before the UI attempts file browsing.
- Reworked `NetdiskApp.tsx` into a beginner-friendly setup page when the mount is missing: the UI now explains that users first log into AList (the underlying mount backend), then configure Baidu/Quark authorization there, and finally return to ClawOS to re-check the mount.
- Added a clearer AList credential display and “打开底层挂载后台 / 我已完成，重新检测” actions so users no longer confuse AList admin login with their Baidu/Quark account login. Added backend route tests for the new netdisk status API. Bumped version to v1.2.5.
- Further refined the Baidu/Quark onboarding UX for non-technical users: added explicit “存储类型 / 挂载路径” cards with one-click copy buttons, plus a step-by-step AList action checklist so users can follow the setup without guessing where to click or what to fill.
- Added a dedicated Cookie acquisition guide to the Baidu/Quark setup flow, with both a browser-extension path (Cookie-Editor) and a manual F12 path, plus direct links to the official netdisk sites and the Cookie-Editor homepage to reduce the biggest remaining onboarding blocker.
- Implemented a new “single-credential auto-config” path for netdisk setup: users can now paste a Baidu `refresh_token` or Quark `cookie` directly in ClawOS, and the backend will create or replace the corresponding AList storage mount automatically, making the AList admin UI an advanced fallback instead of the main flow.
- Implemented the first usable Quark web-login flow inside ClawOS: added a backend proxy for `pan.quark.cn`, persisted captured Set-Cookie headers into a local session file, exposed login-status/reset APIs, and wired the Quark netdisk page to open the embedded login page, poll for a valid login cookie, and auto-configure the Quark mount once detected.

### 2026-03-30 (AI 炒股应用细节完善)
- **What was done**: 
  - 根据 v3.4 架构文档补齐 `AIQuantApp.tsx` 剩余交互细节。
  - 在“策略”模块补充了微型交易表单与历史状态 Timeline。
  - 在“画像”模块补充了针对情绪失控场景的“风险自担确认书”硬核拦截，并增加了 Mood/Stress 及行为偏差克服进度的展示。
  - 在“风控”模块增加了“手动平仓”支持与持仓相关性预警（降低同涨同跌风险）。
  - 在“记忆”模块引入策略版本演进日志展示，凸显系统的自我反思与进化。
- **Key discoveries**: 在前端高保真呈现系统中，通过多步骤的强确认（如：要求输入特定确认文本）是干预“交易行为偏差”的有效 UI 模式。
- **Pending items**: 考虑将后续真实后端的 API 接入（目前均为 Mock 数据）。
